4 Sec. 1. 12 V.S.A. § 1041 is amended to read:
5 § 1041. EXERCISE OF RIGHTS TO FREE SPEECH AND TO PETITION
6 GOVERNMENT FOR REDRESS OF GRIEVANCES; SPECIAL
7 MOTION TO STRIKE
8 (a)(1) This section shall apply to a civil action filed against a person based
9 on the person’s:
10 (A) exercise of the right to freedom of speech or to petition the
11 government on a public issue; and
12 (B) the making of a good faith report or complaint regarding:
13 (i) a violation of 13 V.S.A. chapter 59 (lewdness and prostitution);
14 (ii) a violation of 13 V.S.A. chapter 72 (sexual assault);
15 (iii) a violation of a sexual harassment policy required by 21
16 V.S.A. § 495h or the provisions of 21 V.S.A. § 495h(a) requiring a workplace
17 free from sexual harassment; or
18 (iv) an incident of retaliation for the making of a report or
19 complaint based on subdivisions (i)–(iii) of this subdivision (a)(1)(B), provided
20 the person had a reasonable basis to make such a report or complaint,
21 regardless of whether a criminal, civil, or administration action was initiated.
