6 (b) A special motion to strike under this section shall be filed with the court
7 and served on all parties not more than 60 days after the filing of the
8 complaint. A party may file a response to the motion not more than 15 days
9 after the motion is served on the party. The court may extend the time limits of
10 this subsection for good cause shown.
11 (c)(1) The filing of a special motion to strike under this section shall stay
12 all discovery proceedings in the action. Except as provided in subdivision (2)
13 of this subsection, the stay of discovery shall remain in effect until the court
14 rules on the special motion to strike.
15 (2) The court, on motion and for good cause shown, may order that
16 limited discovery be conducted for the purpose of assisting its decision on the
17 special motion to strike.
18 (d) The court shall hold a hearing on a special motion to strike not more
19 than 30 days after service of the motion unless good cause exists for an
20 extension.
